In any case guess we just hope another mob doesn't fall on day 2 of Ntov. Would suck to loose a statue or Aow spawn due to this. Or if this is the case could we ask to switch places with the next guild in line i guess that could solve the problem is it arose? <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Keep in mind the zones we are talking about; if you're in VT and clearing away, does a guild really care if they miss a KT or Tunare or even AoW? I would suggest that clearing VT would even yeild better than leaving to zap some ssra mobs (that's just me though). <br>
<br>
Morever, however, where ToV is a 2 day event, if a mob pops on your second day, you can get most of the zone done, and then head out as you'd like.<br>
<br>
What do I mean? <br>
<br>
I mean that it will be a very rare occurance indeed that a mob with a 24 hour window will pop at just the right time (approximately 12 hours after the start of a 2 day rotation) to be 'lost' to a guild. If the AoW is up before your ToV North turn, go kill him first, then go into ToV north. <br>
<br>
There is enough leeway that people shouldn't be losing mobs left right and center, and they probaby arn't. <br>
<br>
But again, this comes down to a question of 'what you want more' as a guild. If you're in VT, and it's your turn for Ssra cleanup, well, make the call. Is the last day in VT worth skipping the cleanup? Is the entire North ToV run worth a shot at the Avatar of War?<br>
<br>
The rules make good sense, if not being the most flexible for all guilds, it certainly does present a way to keep guilds who are up for important rotations (ones that drop multiple loot over multiple days) from also getting in on the rotations that drop one or two or four items all at once and are done. <br>
<br>
Like, if we're killing in Tov North, you can be reasonably sure we're going to pass statue; but if we're in our last 6 hours in ToV North and Statue pops, we still have our 24 hour period, as I understand it. <br>
<br>
That, for me, is the only clairification I need; if we've got 6/12/23 hours left in a multiple day rotation, and a mob pops for which we have a 24 hour window, are we forced to pass, or is the onus on us to pass if we don't think we can get to it?<br>
<br>
Inquiring minds...<br>
<br>
Yers,<br>
