<br>
----- Once you enter NToV or VT (for 2 examples of mutli-day rotations), YOU CANNOT LEAVE YOUR MULTI-DAY ROTATION TO KILL ANOTHER ROTATION MOB.<br>
<br>
I don't care what scenario you want to build, the above is what was DECIDED BY THE GUILDS *ON* THE ROTATIONS.<br>
<br>
Just because the answer does not suit you, does not mean your questions were not answered.<br>
<br>
If a guild's turn for KT comes up at the same time their NToV or VT turn comes up: IF they can go kill KT before then enter NToV, that's fine.  IF they can go kill KT after they finish with NToV, that's fine too.  But they CANNOT leave NToV, kill KT, then go back.  A multi-day Rotation will NOT be extended so a guild can also kill their other Rotation mobs. <br>
<br>
The guilds that are on the Rotations are the ones that keep an eye on each other, not the RTA admins. <br>
<br>
And you don't *auto-pass*, you *pass*.  There is a big difference between the two. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=karadin>Karadin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NB-GM<BR>
